title: Led Zeppelin - 1972.02.19 Adelaide, Australia
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1972.02.19 Adelaide, Australia   

Led Zeppelin, Memorial Drive
February 19, 1972, Adelaide, Australia

Audience Recording
Master > DAT

Source: 
Incomplete very good to excellent audience recording. 94 minutes.

Details: 
The tape is a near excellent audience recording from very close to 
the stage. Even though it's an outdoor concert, the recording does 
not "breathe" like many other outdoor recordings. The valiant taper 
was saving tape by pausing the recording between songs.

1. Immigrant Song
2. Heartbreaker
3. Black Dog
4. Since I've Been Loving You
5. Stairway to Heaven
6. Going To California
7. That's The Way
8. Tangerine
9. Bron-Y-Aur Stomp
10. Dazed and Confused
11. Moby Dick
12. Whole Lotta Love

Comments: 
Really great, crisp sound in this powerful and excellent show. The 
opening salvo is awesome, and Jimmy plays one of the best solos in 
Stairway To Heaven, and it's only 1972! Dazed And Confused is truly 
awesome and a riotous medley closes the show. The crowd is going nuts 
throughout the show, with Robert telling them to shut up, and it's 
not hard to see why!
